  • Field Details

    • calibLevel

      @VoDml(id="ds:experiment.ObsDataset.calibLevel", role=attribute, type="ivoa:integer", typeRole=primitiveType) protected Integer calibLevel
      High level classification for the calibration level of the particular dataset as a whole. The calibration level concept conveys to the user information on how much data reduction/processing has been applied to the data. It is up to the data providers to consider how to map their own internal classification to the scale defined here. Scale: 0 - Raw instrumental data, in a proprietary or internal data-provider defined format. 1 - Instrumental data in a standard format (FITS, VOTable, etc ) 2 - Calibrated, science ready data with the instrument signature removed. 3 - Enhanced data products like mosaics, resampled or drizzled images, or heavily processed survey fields. Level 3 data products may represent the combination of data from multiple primary observations. : Attribute calibLevel : multiplicity 0..1

    • derived

      @VoDml(id="ds:experiment.ObsDataset.derived", role=composition, type="ds:experiment.Derived", typeRole=objectType) protected Derived derived
      Provides a high level summary of certain properties of the dataset. Its primary purpose is to support high level filtering of datasets during data discovery. composition derived : ( Multiplicity : 0..1 )

      @VoDml(id="ds:experiment.ObsDataset.target", role=reference, type="ds:experiment.BaseTarget", typeRole=objectType) protected BaseTarget target

    • proposal

      @VoDml(id="ds:experiment.ObsDataset.proposal", role=reference, type="ds:experiment.Proposal", typeRole=objectType) protected Proposal proposal

    • obsConfig

    • ObsDataset

      public ObsDataset(Integer calibLevel, Derived derived, BaseTarget target, Proposal proposal, ObsConfig obsConfig, DataProductType dataProductType, String dataProductSubtype, Curation curation, DataID dataID)
      full parameter constructor.
      Parameters:
      calibLevel - High level classification for the calibration level of the particular dataset as a whole. The calibration level concept conveys to the user information on how much data reduction/processing has been applied to the data. It is up to the data providers to consider how to map their own internal classification to the scale defined here. Scale: 0 - Raw instrumental data, in a proprietary or internal data-provider defined format. 1 - Instrumental data in a standard format (FITS, VOTable, etc ) 2 - Calibrated, science ready data with the instrument signature removed. 3 - Enhanced data products like mosaics, resampled or drizzled images, or heavily processed survey fields. Level 3 data products may represent the combination of data from multiple primary observations.
      derived - Provides a high level summary of certain properties of the dataset. Its primary purpose is to support high level filtering of datasets during data discovery.
      target - Reference to a BaseTarget object from Observation. Provides metadata describing the target of the observation.
      proposal - Reference to Proposal object from Observation. This object provides metadata identifying any proposal related to the observation which produced the dataset.
      obsConfig - Reference to ObsConfig object from Observation. This object provides some high-level metadata related to the observation configuration.
      dataProductType - Describes the high level scientific classification of the data content. Values are restricted to the DataProductType enumeration set and convey the general idea of the content and organization of a dataset.
      dataProductSubtype - Secondary type classification for the dataset. This field is intended to precisely specify the scientific nature of the data product, possibly in terms relevant only to a specific archive or data collection. For example, dataProductType='image' could have associated dataProductSubtype='src.image', 'bkg.image', 'PixelMask', etc. Values are unrestricted strings.
      curation - Provides metadata related to the entity responsible for the curation of the dataset.
      dataID - DataID provides high level identification metadata for the dataset itself, and any associations with various collections.
